caption: Do you think death rays would be considered electronics or sporting goods?
What do they mean "Space for Rent"?
If they know where we are, then they’re more advanced than we thought.
To Bed, Bath, and Beyond!
Dairy Queen, that must be their leader
What happened to Radio Shack? Now we'll never get home.
Let's start with a store that sell pants.
We found earth. We’ll find Target.
I assume their leader is this “Burger King.”
So, this is where earthlings go before they shop online.
The currency exchange store has to be the one called Starbucks.
Admit it—you forgot what level we landed on.
If I could read a map we wouldn't be here.
Their ability to track us has advanced significantly.
We can still get home. I saw a sign "space available"
We’re good; they’re all looking at their phones.
I thought this was a strip mall!
Cancel the invasion -- they know we are here.
I've never heard of planet fitness.
You guided us for thousands of light-years without getting lost, but you can’t remember which entrance we used?
Oh sure, now you look at a map.
These earthlings are smarter than we thought, they know exactly where we are!
These humans are very clever, they already know where we are
Wait, was it "conquer the mall" or "conquer them all"?
Should we abduct one now, or wait until they go on sale?"
We knew they were litigious- but a food court?
Now all we need is a map of the galaxies.
Always the map! Why won't you ask someone?
You said this was uncharted territory.
They deny our existence but know where we are?
